<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-12-20T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-12-20T13:00:00-05:00" n="144" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d144">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/227</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-12-20T18:00:00+00:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 20, 1916, 6 p. m.</hi>
                                </date>
                                <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 7 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>5352. Your circular 18th<note n="1" xml:id="d144fn1">
                                <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_97">p.
                                97</ref>.</note> presented to Lord <persName corresp="#p_CEARV1">Robert Cecil</persName>, Colonial [and Acting?] Foreign Secretary,
                            precisely as instructed. He remarked that obviously he could now make no
                            comment; but his interest in it was great and I repeated and emphasized
                            the disinterested earnestness of the President.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_PWH1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Page</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>